The paper deals with the analysis of an evolutionary algorithm on a benchmark function, which falls under the scope of computational intelligence and optimization (cs.NE). The analysis involves understanding the correlation between decision variables, which is a topic of interest in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the impact of selective pressure on the algorithm's performance, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
